g.com/photo/msid-132327047,imgsize-1655123.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Canada gives share of bridge profits to US to get Trump nod]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132339859.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The Gordie Howe International Bridge will open on July 27 connecting Detroit and Windsor. Canada agreed to share net toll profits with the United States after construction costs. This agreement resolves a long-standing dispute between the two trading partners. Canada funded the entire $4.5 billion construction project over the Detroit River. The deal directs proceeds to a US-run regional development fund.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/canada-gives-share-of-bridge-profits-to-us-to-get-trump-nod/articleshow/132339859.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/canada-gives-share-of-bridge-profits-to-us-to-get-trump-nod/articleshow/132339859.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T07:26:29+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132339867,imgsize-112138.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bangladesh bars media from publishing Hasina statements]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132339829.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Bangladesh's government has ordered all media to stop broadcasting Sheikh Hasina's statements. This directive follows a court ban on publishing content from the former prime minister. Several outlets published an interview with Hasina, which prompted the government's action. A journalist stated Hasina remains the country's paramount leader and should have security. She has been the target of past assassination attempts and attacks.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/bangladesh-bars-media-from-publishing-hasina-statements/articleshow/132339829.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/bangladesh-bars-media-from-publishing-hasina-statements/articleshow/132339829.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T07:19:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Ahsan Tasnim</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132339837,imgsize-669816.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russians urged to work from home amid fuel crisis]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132339820.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Russia's Novosibirsk region is urging remote work and reduced car travel. This comes amid a deepening fuel crisis affecting many Russian areas. Ukrainian strikes on oil refineries have significantly impacted fuel supplies. One major facility in Omsk was recently disabled by an attack. This situation has led to fuel shortages and rationing across Russia.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/russians-urged-to-work-from-home-amid-fuel-crisis/articleshow/132339820.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/russians-urged-to-work-from-home-amid-fuel-crisis/articleshow/132339820.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T07:16:57+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132339824,imgsize-181914.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Martha Lillard, last US polio patient using iron lung, dies]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132339812.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/martha-lillard-last-us-polio-patient-using-iron-lung-dies/articleshow/132339812.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/martha-lillard-last-us-polio-patient-using-iron-lung-dies/articleshow/132339812.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T07:13:50+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132339814,imgsize-1124975.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[US employers told to fire foreign workers who are on the way to lose Temporary Protected Status]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132337638.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-employers-told-to-fire-foreign-workers-who-are-on-the-way-to-lose-temporary-protected-status/articleshow/132337638.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-employers-told-to-fire-foreign-workers-who-are-on-the-way-to-lose-temporary-protected-status/articleshow/132337638.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-12T02:29:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132337642,imgsize-96656.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Jill Biden: "Good marriages push us -- not to become someone else but to become the best version of ourselves"]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132337538.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-jill-biden-good-marriages-push-us-not-to-become-someone-else-but-to-become-the-best-version-of-ourselves/articleshow/132337538.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-jill-biden-good-marriages-push-us-not-to-become-someone-else-but-to-become-the-best-version-of-ourselves/article